  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<h3 id=\"id-1.19.1-NewFeatures\">New Features</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RQDEV/pages/1640071169/Catalog+Quick+Create\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1640071169\" data-linked-resource-version=\"20\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Quick Create</a></p><ul><li><p>Quick Create allows users to add new catalog items and onhand quantities without leaving a ticket.</p></li><li><p>Quick Create is also available when creating a new Purchase Order.</p></li><li><p>The catalog can be sorted by Created Item Context, so Managers can see details about when, by whom, and by which process catalog items were created.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3 id=\"id-1.19.1-BugFixes\">Bug Fixes</h3><ul><li><p>Fixed an issue affecting the Weekly Total column of the Attendance page.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue that restricted users outside of the Manager role from selecting the Repair Complete status on tickets.</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue for some users where Reorder Points set by location override were not triggering items to be reordered.</p></li></ul>",
      "representation": "export_view",
